Property.name: CrystalPreviewMode
Property.Description: Crystal Preview Mode for V10

Parameter.name: MAJORVERSION
Parameter.Description: Used by Patching to determine the Version <<MAJORVERSION>>.<<SUBVERSION>> e.g. 6.9 Used by TPS and other VB apps to determine whether to run newer code or not <<MAJORVERSION>>.<<MINORVERSION>> e.g. 6.57

Parameter.name: SUBVERSION
Parameter.Description: Used by Patching to determine the Version <<MAJORVERSION>>.<<SUBVERSION>> e.g. 6.9 Must be incremented for w650 when a new release is cut

Parameter.name: MINORVERSION
Parameter.Description: Used by TPS and other VB apps to determine whether to run newer code or not <<MAJORVERSION>>.<<MINORVERSION>> e.g. 6.57 Must be incremented for w650 when a new release is cut

Property.name: CrystalRptLicenses
Property.Description: Total number of Crystal Reports licenses for the Organisation. See also PrintService Class

Property.name: CrystalViewerType
Property.Description: Crystal Viewer Type

Property.name: DSN
Property.Description: This property has been for a long time but as far as we can tell is not being used any more. It is about to be reused as the Default Crystal DSN, that the TPS will use as the ODBC DSN for a Report

Property.name: DataNamespace
Property.Description: Data NameSpace

Property.name: DecimalPlaces
Property.Description: Number of decimal places used by currency conversions

Property.name: DecimalSymbol
Property.Description: Decimal symbol

Property.name: LanguageApp
Property.Description: Stores rowid from SSLanguage table. Uses this language when first logging on, then user's language overrides.

Property.name: LayoutManager
Property.Description: Connection string to the TRak Web Edit Layout manager for this connection. For example: cn_iptcp:127.0.0.1[1972]:W641 Which identifies: the server IP address. 127.0.0.1 in this example. the server port. 1972 in this example. the namespace. W641 in this example.

Property.name: OverrideAuthentication
Property.Description: Override MEDTRAK authentication. Should only be enabled where authentication is provided externally to MEDTRAK - e.g. IIS + NT, LDAP

Property.name: PathToApp
Property.Description: The path from top level on web server to application e.g. if app is located under http://www.trak.com.au/appname then '/appname' is the 'PathToApp' Used when web reports are printed from Cache and by the test print facilty. Used in conjunction with WebServer

Property.name: PathToCDLs
Property.Description: Path used to import CDLS, views, and to export views from the ViewBuilder

Property.name: PathToDSFiles
Property.Description: Path of the folder that will store all Discharge Summary PDFs and text files.

Property.name: PathToScripts
Property.Description: The path on the server for generated scripts to be written to. Used only in publishing generated scripts.

Property.name: PathToReports
Property.Description: The path to reports folder. Used by the TPS when printing a report.

Property.name: PathToTemporaryFiles
Property.Description: Used by Mail and Fax services as common place to put attatchments. Must be a UNC path Also used by AutoPatch fro remote patching ...

Property.name: PathToTemporaryFilesUnix
Property.Description: For unix boxes only this is the local path of the PathtoTemporary files. Normal users can leave this field blank.

Property.name: PathToVBFileServerRoot
Property.Description: UNC path to Patches folder. There should only one folder in use for patching.

Property.name: PathToVBPatches
Property.Description: UNC path to Patches folder. There should only one folder in use for patching.

Property.name: PathToWebPatches
Property.Description: UNC path to Patches folder. There should only one folder in use for patching.

Property.name: PathsToWebServers
Property.Description: A ; delimitted list of Web Server paths. There may be any number of Web Application Servers attached to the same medtrak database. All Paths should be UNC paths.

Property.name: PrintServiceEnabled
Property.Description:
Enables/Disables Crystal reports license monitoring. When enabled Crystal reports go into the PrintHistory queue with a status of Waiting and are later processed by the Trak Print Service.
When it is disabled, Print Requests for Crystal reports are handled directly by webesys.Printrpt.asp ... see websys.Report.PrintReport()

Property.name: SMTPServer
Property.Description: DNS Name or IP address of SMTP (Simple Mail Transport Protocol) server. SMTP server must be accessible via TCP from the Cache server.

Property.name: SiteCode
Property.Description: A code to identify the site

Property.name: SortMaxRows
Property.Description: The maximum number of rows to be returned and sorted before aborting sort.

Property.name: TimeOut
Property.Description: Application TimeOut in minutes

Property.name: UseEPRMenuScroll
Property.Description: true to use system scroll buttons on epr menu headers. false if want to use site left/right menus.

Property.name: VBFolderNameActiveX
Property.Description: UNC path to Patches folder. There should only one folder in use for patching.

Property.name: VBFolderNameActiveXWinSys
Property.Description: UNC path to Patches folder. There should only one folder in use for patching.

Property.name: VBFolderNameExecutables
Property.Description: UNC path to Patches folder. There should only one folder in use for patching.

Property.name: WebServer
Property.Description: Address (IP Address or Name of web server). Used when web prints are generated from cache and by the test print facility. Used in conjunction with PathToApp.

Property.name: Region
Property.Description: ab 1.06.07 63290 - region is a higher level than site (eg. Australia)

Property.Description: dah 15.02.2008 66325 - add default email from for CS
